    "Before capturing speeds, calibrate by marking a known distance in a photo — like a lane width or parking space. You'll start on the Calibrate tab where you can also choose imperial or metric units." : {
      "extractionState" : "stale",
      "localizations" : {
        "en" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Before capturing speeds, calibrate by marking a known distance in a photo — like a lane width or parking space. You'll start on the Calibrate tab where you can also choose imperial or metric units."
          }
        },
        "es-MX" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Antes de capturar velocidades, calibra marcando una distancia conocida en una foto — como el ancho de un carril o un cajón de estacionamiento. Empezarás en la pestaña Calibrar donde también puedes elegir unidades imperiales o métricas."
          }
